                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord and in the power of His might. Put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil. For we do not wrestle against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the darkness of this age, against spiritual hosts of wickedness in the heavenly places. Therefore take up the whole armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand.”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:10-13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“But He answered and said, “It is written, ‘Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.’ ””
                                                                            <b>Matthew 4:4 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Stand therefore, having girded your waist with truth...
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:14-a NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“You therefore must endure hardship as a good soldier of Jesus Christ. No one engaged in warfare entangles himself with the affairs of this life, that he may please him who enlisted him as a soldier.”
                                                                            <b>II Timothy 2:3-4 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We are all called to be good soldiers of Jesus Christ. Our battle is with the same Satan that brought Eve to sin and turned  her away from God in Eden.  Just as with Eve Satan wants to attack God’s character, and every believers character because we stand in our rightful place once again, “in the image of God.”  His sometimes blatant and other times subtle schemes seem to be unending, as in the Garden casting doubt, persecution, peer pressure, initiating confusion, division in the body, temptation to sin...the list goes on and on.
                                                                            God alone is eternal, He only reigns supreme, that is where our focus need be.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our mission is to take up the whole armor of God, that we may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all to stand.  We notice it is the “armor of God,” it is His armor so we are clothed “in Him.”  This is the only way we can withstand the wiles of  the devil. Satan comes with lies as he is the father of lies as said in <b>John 8:44.</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We believers must know the truth so the first piece of the armor put in place is the foundation for the rest of the armor. It is the Belt of Truth.  The Belt protects the abdomen and is used to tie down the tunic the soldier wears.   Truth as in the Word of God, truth as in standing in integrity, against insincerity, hypocrisy, falsifications and dishonesty of every kind, and more.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As Jesus was in the wilderness and being tempted by Satan He said,  “It is written, ‘Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We concentrate this day on, ‘it is written...and every word that proceeds from the mouth of God. We will come back to this complete verse on another day.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I assume we are all blessed to own a bible, some might have many of various versions.  Each one of these bibles we own are our connection to the Belt of Truth, because the Bible is the Truth, and we are to read and come to know the truth empowered by the Holy Spirit and apply these truths to our lives.  I dare say we are without excuse.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Secondly we are to walk out these truths we have read and applied to our lives to the honor and glory for the one we serve.  To stand in battle and properly wear the belt of truth one must not play in the devils playground . We must not engage with him in the affairs of this life he would like to entangle us in.  As soldiers in God’s army we are committed to the Lord Jesus Christ and His ways.  To stand against the enemy there is no room for anything less...one can’t put on the rest of the armor and win the battle without representing complete truth.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We fight the good fight walking in the truth of  the Word of God, and in standing  in moral soundness, walking in the truths He has taught us.  This is girding our waists with the belt of  truth.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Lord may we reassess our walk with You. Into Your hand we commit our spirit; You have redeemed us , O Lord God of Truth. Help us to desire to walk in the truths of Your word, as You tell us having done all to stand, we stand in the integrity You have called us to.  Not by might, nor by power but by Your Spirit.  In Jesus name.
                                                                        </p>
